PRIVACY POLICY

At Chainsplorer, based on (earth), we are committed to safeguarding your personal data. This policy explains how we, along with our subsidiaries and holding company (collectively referred to as “Chainsplorer Wallet” or “we”), collect, use, and protect your information.

By visiting our website at https://chainsplorer.com/ (referred to as our “Site”) or utilizing Chainsplorer Wallet and any related applications or software (collectively termed our “App”), you consent to the practices described in this policy.

Information We Collect

To fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, we may gather and process various types of information, including:

Information You Provide: This includes any personal details you share with us, such as your name, address, email, phone number, credit card information, and other identifiers. You might provide this information when you:

Report an issue,
Access specific features on our Site or App,
Request support, or
Participate in surveys or questionnaires.
Information We Collect Automatically: We automatically gather data when you visit our Site or use our App, including:

Technical details like your IP address, browser type, and operating system,
Information about your visit, including URLs visited, products viewed, and the time spent on pages,
Data from Third Parties: We may receive information about you from third-party partners, including service providers, analytics companies, and advertising networks. We will inform you when we receive such information and how we intend to use it.
We retain personal data only as long as necessary for the specified purposes. Data may be archived if the purpose for its collection continues.

How We Use Your Information

We utilize the information we collect for various purposes, such as:

Enhancing and developing our services,
Researching and launching new features or products,
Presenting content effectively on our Site and App,
Sending you updates and alerts about our services,
Engaging in legal proceedings or seeking advice,
Responding to your inquiries and requests, and
Pursuing purposes related to the above.
Disclosure of Information

While we keep your personal data confidential, you agree that we may share information with:

Other members of our group, including subsidiaries and our ultimate holding company,
Employees, contractors, and service providers involved in our operations (such as customer support staff),
Our international offices, affiliates, and partners (on a need-to-know basis),
Individuals bound by confidentiality obligations to us,
Entities required to receive disclosures under applicable laws, and
Potential transferees of our operations.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies

Our Site uses cookies to enhance your experience. Cookies are small files stored on your device that help us recognize you during future visits.

We use different types of cookies, including:

Essential Cookies: Necessary for the basic functionality of our Site,
Performance Cookies: Help us analyze visitor behavior and improve the user experience,
Functionality Cookies: Allow us to personalize your experience by remembering your preferences.
You can block cookies through your browser settings, but doing so may limit your access to certain features of our Site.

We may also use third-party services that employ cookies and other tracking technologies to help us analyze how users interact with our Site and improve our services. The information collected may be shared with these service providers.

Links to Third-Party Websites

Our Site and App may contain links to external websites that we do not control. We encourage you to review their privacy policies, as we cannot be responsible for their practices.

Data Security

We prioritize the security of your information. All data you provide is stored on secure servers. Access to your personal information is limited to authorized personnel only, who are subject to confidentiality agreements.

While we implement various security measures, please note that no method of transmission over the Internet is completely secure. Any data you transmit is at your own risk.

Your Rights

You have the right to:

Verify if we hold personal data about you,
Access the personal data we have on file,
Request corrections to any inaccuracies in your data.
Requests under this section may incur a small administrative fee.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this policy occasionally, and any changes will be posted on our Site. Continuing to use our Site and App after modifications indicates your acceptance of the updated terms.

Languages

In case of discrepancies between the English and any other language versions of this policy, the English version will take precedence.

